# Terminal Virtual Environment

Whenever a terminal is opened or shell commands are run in this workspace, ensure the Python virtual environment is active.

## Guidelines

- **Activate venv first**: When opening a new terminal or running Python-dependent commands, activate the virtual environment before other commands.
- **Preferred paths** (check project root): `.venv` or `venv`

### Activation commands

| Platform | Command |
|----------|---------|
| Windows (PowerShell) | `.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1` or `.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1` |
| Windows (CMD) | `venv\Scripts\activate.bat` or `.venv\Scripts\activate.bat` |
| Unix / macOS | `source venv/bin/activate` or `source .venv/bin/activate` |

### When the agent runs shell commands

- Run the appropriate activation command before `pip`, `python`, `pytest`, or other Python tools
- Or use the venv's executable directly, e.g. `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest` (Windows)
